g.text: Disk image is a flat, uninitialized blob of zeros on host filesystem.
Block 0 is defined. Filesystem geometry is now durable.
All blocks and inodes marked FREE. Inode table initialized to NULL.
Inode 1 (Root) allocated. Points to first data block containing '.' and '..'.
Resource usage reflected in bitmaps to prevent root data overwrite.
Free counts updated. All buffers flushed to physical media.
